28
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:22,118
Let's have the <i>geotjeori.</i>

29
00:03:25,288 --> 00:03:26,830
Is instant rice okay?

30
00:03:26,831 --> 00:03:30,584
Do you really want to give
your father-in-law instant rice?

31
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:33,171
But you made me instant rice
last time too.

32
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:36,007
Cook some rice so it scorches.

33
00:03:40,178 --> 00:03:41,011
You punk...

34
00:03:41,012 --> 00:03:43,513
- I'll go buy some rice.
- Don't you have any rice?

35
00:03:43,514 --> 00:03:47,769
If you want scorched rice,
I have some instant scorched rice.

36
00:03:49,020 --> 00:03:51,104
No, I mean...

37
00:03:51,105 --> 00:03:54,524
- I can make it from instant rice.
- I just want freshly cooked rice.

38
00:03:54,525 --> 00:03:56,818
- Well...
- I eat instant rice every day.

39
00:03:56,819 --> 00:04:00,864
<i>The ERPB's approval ratings
have topped 50% for the first time.</i>

40
00:04:00,865 --> 00:04:03,200
<i>In a survey
of potential presidential candidates,</i>

41
00:04:03,201 --> 00:04:07,788
<i>Minister Choi Gang-seok's approval rating
has surged compared to the previous poll.</i>

42
00:04:07,789 --> 00:04:11,708
<i>Some believe he has hit the nail
on the head about the public's concerns.</i>

43
00:04:11,709 --> 00:04:13,293
<i>That's right.</i>

44
00:04:13,294 --> 00:04:17,506
<i>The ERPB has yet to shake the label of
"a group that acts on personal vendettas."</i>

45
00:04:17,507 --> 00:04:21,343
<i>Since the ERPB's key members
are the deceased female teacher's family,</i>

46
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:22,929
<i>it is likely that...</i>

